cs.HC, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.SD, cs.CY 

This paper discusses the difficulties of evoking ethnic cues in a robot and proposes an approach to overcome those difficulties based on using ethnically salient behaviors. The paper focuses on the interaction between humans and robots, which falls under the category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). The use of behaviors to express ethnicity in a robot character involves robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The study also evaluates the possibility of achieving the homophily effect, which relates to social dynamics (cs.SD) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
